<paragraph id="E927751BFF8EFFBDFF1BE86BFBADFF06" blockId="3.[136,1452,1634,2093]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1452,158,617]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="297" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFF1BE86BFF5BF9A6" bold="true" box="[136,192,1634,1660]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">Note</emphasis>
:—The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF8EFFBAFE22E86AFCF8F9A6" authority="(Brown 1915: 202 - 203)" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityPageNumber="202 - 203" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[433,867,1634,1661]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosa">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFE22E86AFE24F9A7" box="[433,447,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFE5FE86BFDCBF9A6" box="[460,592,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">suffruticosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF8EFFBAFDCDE86BFCC0F9A6" author="Brown, N. E." box="[606,859,1634,1661]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" pagination="185 - 261" refId="ref5113" refString="Brown, N. E. (1915) Sansevieria. A monograph of all known species. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information (Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew) 1915: 185 - 261. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4107465" type="journal article" year="1915">Brown 1915: 202–203</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
describes the leaves as “rough throughout or smooth at the basal part and rough above”, the perianth tube “about 5 lin. [= 
<quantity id="2E60D8FEFF8EFFBAFC1FE88FFC68F97B" box="[908,1011,1670,1697]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
] long” and cites “ 
<collectingCountry id="918F358BFF8EFFBAFB2FE88EFA04F945" box="[1212,1439,1670,1697]" name="Kenya" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">BRITISH EAST AFRICA</collectingCountry>
” [the territory of Kenya according to the locality today], Nairobi River Falls, scarce, 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFBD0E8A3FB27F91E" box="[1091,1212,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">Powell, 13</emphasis>
! and without precise locality, 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFF7AE8C6FEB6F932" box="[233,301,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">Evans</emphasis>
s.n.
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFECEE8C6FEFDF933" box="[349,358,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">!</emphasis>
”, as 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF8EFFBAFE32E8C6FD9CF933" box="[417,519,1743,1769]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">syntypes</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF8EFFBAFD81E8C7FD51F933" author="Pfennig, H." box="[530,714,1742,1769]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" pagination="169 - 179" refId="ref6569" refString="Pfennig, H. (1981 b) Zur Systematik und Kultur einiger ostafrikanischer Sansevieria - Arten (Agavaceae). Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 102: 169 - 179." type="journal article" year="1981">Pfennig (1981b)</bibRefCitation>
found that his cultivated flowering plants and specimens at Kew fell into two discontinuous groups with perianth tube lengths of 
<quantity id="2E60D8FEFF8EFFBAFCF2E8FBFC56F8D7" box="[865,973,1778,1805]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13 mm</quantity>
and 
<quantity id="2E60D8FEFF8EFFBAFB95E8FBFB19F8D7" box="[1030,1154,1778,1805]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="18.0">18–24 mm</quantity>
, with cultivated flowering plants from the type locality of his 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF8EFFBAFD98E91EFD3EF8EA" authorityName="Byng &amp; Christenhusz" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Pfennig" box="[523,677,1814,1841]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="longituba">
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFDA9E91FFD3EF8EA" box="[570,677,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">longituba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Nairobi River Falls having perianth tubes 
<quantity id="2E60D8FEFF8EFFBAFB0BE91FFA8BF8EB" box="[1176,1296,1814,1841]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="22.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="20.0">20–24 mm</quantity>
long. Pfennig further concluded that N.E. Brown must have based his protologue on cultivated flowering plants of 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFA93E932FAEFF88E" box="[1280,1396,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">Evans s.n.</emphasis>
, and that he had not seen flowering material for the specimen 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFC88E957FC15F8A2" box="[795,910,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">Powell 13</emphasis>
. Pfennig could not locate the specimen 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFACDE957FF3FF846" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">Powell 13</emphasis>
cited by N.E. Brown at Kew. He described the long-tubed plants which are distributed south of the line Mau Escarpment – Aberdares – Mt. Kenya as 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF8EFFBAFDC3E9AEFB11F81A" authority="Pfennig (1981 b: 178)" authorityName="Pfennig" authorityPageNumber="178" authorityYear="1981" box="[592,1162,1958,1985]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="longituba">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFDC3E9AEFD6BF81A" box="[592,752,1958,1985]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">S. suffruticosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFCB5E9AFFC0AF81A" box="[806,913,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">longituba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF8EFFBAFC0BE9AFFB11F81A" author="Pfennig, H." box="[920,1162,1958,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" pagination="169 - 179" refId="ref6569" refString="Pfennig, H. (1981 b) Zur Systematik und Kultur einiger ostafrikanischer Sansevieria - Arten (Agavaceae). Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 102: 169 - 179." type="journal article" year="1981">Pfennig (1981b: 178)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, geographically separated from the short-perianth tubed 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF8EFFBAFE44E9C2FCAAF83E" authority="var. suffruticosa" box="[471,817,1994,2021]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="suffruticosa">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFE44E9C2FDECF83E" box="[471,631,1994,2021]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">S. suffruticosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFD3EE9C3FCAAF83E" box="[685,817,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">suffruticosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed north of that line. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF8EFFBAFBECE9C2FAF9F83F" author="Newton, L. E." box="[1151,1378,1994,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" pagination="224 - 226" refId="ref6156" refString="Newton, L. E. (2000) A beautiful new species of Sansevieria (Dracaenaceae) in Kenya. Cactus and Succulent Journal 72: 224 - 226." type="journal article" year="2000">Newton (2000: 225)</bibRefCitation>
added that 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF8EFFBAFF29E9E6FE65F7D2" authorityName="Pfennig" authorityYear="1981" box="[186,510,2030,2057]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="longituba">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFF29E9E6FEC0F7D2" box="[186,347,2030,2057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">S. suffruticosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFE00E9E7FE65F7D2" box="[403,510,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">longituba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smooth leaves, in contrast to rough leaves in 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF8EFFBAFBA1E9E6FA0BF7D2" authority="var. suffruticosa" box="[1074,1424,2030,2057]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="suffruticosa">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFBA1E9E6FB48F7D2" box="[1074,1235,2030,2057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">S. suffruticosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF8EFFBAFA9FE9E7FA0BF7D2" box="[1292,1424,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="296">suffruticosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a further character separating both taxa which was overlooked by Pfennig. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF8EFFBAFC2FE61AFAB0F7F7" author="Byng, J. W. &amp; Christenhusz, J. M. M." box="[956,1323,2066,2093]" pageId="3" pageNumber="296" pagination="64 - 67" refId="ref5266" refString="Byng, J. W. &amp; Christenhusz, J. M. M. (2018) Asparagaceae. In: Christenhusz, J. M. M., Fay, F. M. &amp; Byng, J. W. (Eds.) The Global Flora. A practical flora to vascular plant species of the world. Special Edition. GLOVAP Nomenclature 1, vol. 4. Plant Gateway Ltd., Bradford, pp. 64 - 67." type="book chapter" year="2018">Byng &amp; Christenhusz (2018: 67)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this taxon into 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF89FFBDFEA3EE96FE3BFF62" authorityName="Vandelli ex Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[304,416,159,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFEA3EE96FE3BFF62" box="[304,416,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the rank of variety following the rank assignment of the protologue, but since it differs in two features and is geographically separate, subspecific rank is deemed appropriate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1822690FF89FFBDFF2EEEEFFE64FCC6" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" type="description">
<paragraph id="E927751BFF89FFBDFF2EEEEFFA03FE6F" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFF2EEEEFFED6FEDA" bold="true" box="[189,333,230,256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Typification</emphasis>
:—To implement the correct application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF89FFBDFC52EEEEFBFEFEDA" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[961,1125,230,257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosa">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFC52EEEEFBFEFEDA" box="[961,1125,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">S. suffruticosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF89FFBDFBEAEEEFFAA9FEDA" box="[1145,1330,230,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="suffruticosa">
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFB3DEEEFFAA9FEDA" box="[1198,1330,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">suffruticosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF89FFBDFADDEEEFFF66FEFF" author="Mbugua, P. K." pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="10 - 41" refId="ref6106" refString="Mbugua, P. K. (2007) Sansevieria. In: Beentje, H. J. &amp; Ghazanfar, S. A. (Eds.) Flora of Tropical East Africa. Dracaenaceae. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, pp. 10 - 41." type="book chapter" year="2007">Mbugua (2007: 26)</bibRefCitation>
designated one of the two collections of 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFD54EF02FC90FEFE" box="[711,779,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Evans</emphasis>
at Kew; 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFCE3EF02FC79FEFE" box="[880,994,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Evans s.n.</emphasis>
(
<date id="9D2653DBFF89FFBDFC62EF03FB06FEFE" box="[1009,1181,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" value="1911-03-17">17 March 1911</date>
, 2 cross-labelled sheets, K 255770 &amp; K 255771 digital images! available at: http://specimens.kew.org/herbarium/K000255770 &amp; http:// specimens.kew.org/herbarium/K000255771) as the 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF89FFBDFD58EF5BFCAEFEB6" box="[715,821,338,364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFC76EF5AFBC3FEB6" box="[997,1112,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Evans s.n.</emphasis>
(
<date id="9D2653DBFF89FFBDFBFBEF5BFA9DFEB6" box="[1128,1286,338,364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" value="1909-10-12">Oct. 12. 1909</date>
, K 000255772 digital image!, available at: http://specimens.kew.org/herbarium/K000255772)) represents a 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF89FFBDFB29EF7EFA8EFE4B" box="[1210,1301,375,401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">syntype</typeStatus>
; the 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF89FFBDFAC7EF7EFA30FE4B" box="[1364,1451,375,401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">syntype</typeStatus>
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFF1BEF93FF62FE6E" box="[136,249,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Powell 13</emphasis>
is presumed lost (
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF89FFBDFE57EF93FDF5FE6F" author="Pfennig, H." box="[452,622,410,437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="169 - 179" refId="ref6569" refString="Pfennig, H. (1981 b) Zur Systematik und Kultur einiger ostafrikanischer Sansevieria - Arten (Agavaceae). Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 102: 169 - 179." type="journal article" year="1981">Pfennig 1981b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF89FFBDFD11EF92FCE8FE6E" author="Newton, L. E." box="[642,883,410,437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" refId="ref6357" refString="Newton, L. E. (2020) Sansevieria. In: Eggli, U. &amp; Nyffeler, R. (Eds.) Illustrated Handbook of Succulent Plants, 2 nd ed., Monocotyledons, Vol. 2. Springer, Berlin, pp. 1353 - 1385. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 662 - 56486 - 8 _ 29" type="book" year="2020">Newton (2020: 1380)</bibRefCitation>
imprecisely cited the “type” as “Evans s.n. [K]”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E927751BFF89FFBDFF2EEFB7FE8EFDB2" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">
The “ 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF89FFBDFF68EFB7FEF9FE02" box="[251,354,446,472]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">holotype</typeStatus>
” of 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF89FFBDFE07EFB6FD40FE02" authorityName="Pfennig" authorityYear="1981" box="[404,731,446,473]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="suffruticosa" variety="longituba">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFE07EFB6FDADFE02" box="[404,566,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">S. suffruticosa</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFDE3EFB7FD40FE02" box="[624,731,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">longituba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cited in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF89FFBDFC67EFB7FB4CFE02" author="Pfennig, H." box="[1012,1239,446,472]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="169 - 179" refId="ref6569" refString="Pfennig, H. (1981 b) Zur Systematik und Kultur einiger ostafrikanischer Sansevieria - Arten (Agavaceae). Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 102: 169 - 179." type="journal article" year="1981">Pfennig 1981b: 178</bibRefCitation>
) as “ 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFA87EFB7FA30FE02" box="[1300,1451,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Pfennig 1336</emphasis>
(EA)” consists of two sheets which are not cross-labelled (EA000002615 &amp; EA000002616 see above), thus actually representing 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF89FFBDFE8FEC0EFEE5FDFB" box="[284,382,519,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">syntypes</typeStatus>
(ICN Article 9.6, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D0908EAFF89FFBDFDC7EC0FFCADFDFA" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[596,822,518,544]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" refId="ref6937" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFD26EC0EFD6BFDFA" box="[693,752,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Both sheets consist of a plant with inflorescence and flowers. The specimen EA000002615 which better illustrates the long perianth tube of the flowers is designated here as 
<typeStatus id="3623CBB9FF89FFBDFF35EC47FE8BFDB2" box="[166,272,590,616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E927751BFF89FFBDFF1BEC9EFEB8FD6A" blockId="4.[136,291,663,688]" box="[136,291,663,688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFF1BEC9EFEB8FD6A" box="[136,291,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">New synonym</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E927751BFF89FFBDFF1BECD7FE64FCC6" blockId="4.[136,1451,734,796]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">
The following recently published infraspecific taxon is referred to the synonymy so that no new combination for its transfer into 
<taxonomicName id="2E980E98FF89FFBDFE84ED0AFE1CFCC6" authorityName="Vandelli ex Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[279,391,771,796]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBECA909FF89FFBDFE84ED0AFE1CFCC6" box="[279,391,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Dracaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
